Ten international firms and consortiums have expressed interest in the contract to expand the Nairobi-Nakuru-Mau Summit road.Kenha called for applications on November 9 last year. The application deadline was on Saturday. Project Prequalification Committee chairman George Kiiru said, &ldquo;We are sure the evaluation will yield strong candidates.&rdquo;He did not disclose the firms. The contract includes maintenance to ensure the roads remain in an ultramodern condition.The Nairobi-Nakuru-Mau Summit road is part of the Northern Corridor and among the most important roads in the region, used to transport cargo from the Port of Mombasa and Nairobi. Kenha chief Peter Mundinia said the project will significantly reduce the travel time between Nairobi and Mau Summit.